narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Greater knowledge of the field, key texts of the discipline, improved skills in analysis

I learned about the history of gender and sex. What the terms have encompassed historically and how it has shifted including the impacts that it has had on people. The discussions in class were always very nuanced and open allowing for deep thought and reflection.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I felt there was a good range of material with different perspectives, I simply wish it could have been longer but I understand the limits of a summer course time-wise. Would have appreciated more material specifically focused on nonbinary perspectives, as a lot of the sources (often because of the time of writing) were still positioned in a binary gender framework

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would recommend this course, as I feel I learned a lot and had an engaging experience
Yes, I think taking this course was a really good decision and if you are willing to learn you get a lot out of it.
